A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Department of State Police – Residency Requirements
3 FOR the purpose of altering the residency requirements for police employees of the
4 Department of State Police; and generally relating to residency requirements of
5 employees of the Department of State Police.
6 BY repealing and reenacting, with amendments,
7 Article – Public Safety
8 Section 2–402
9 Annotated Code of Maryland
10 (2022 Replacement Volume and 2024 Supplement)
11 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
12 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
13 Article – Public Safety
14 2–402.
15 (a) (1) In accordance with the State budget, the Secretary shall appoint the
16 employees that the Secretary considers necessary for the efficient administration of the
17 Department.
18 (2) The Secretary shall make each appointment from a list of eligible
19 candidates in accordance with the State Personnel and Pensions Article.
20 (b) Each CIVILIAN appointee to the Department shall:
21 (1) be a resident of the State on the date of appointment; and
